pproach to mapping through decolonial aesthetics and poetic thinking, the three essays in this volume help define a film studies perspective on mapping as a practice that structures political and aesthetic regimes, organizes and communicates shared realities, but also enables dissenting reconfigurations of concretely experienced worlds.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aMapping. 4aPostcolonialismus. 4afilmisches Erlebnis. 4averkörperte Mobilitäten. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aMapping.  acinematic experience.  aembodied mobilities.  apostcolonialism.1 aCarter, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalcomess, Bettina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMalcomess, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRositzka, Eileen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRositzka, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107690500 cprintz978311076898540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/97831